## O. QUICK WINS / MEDIUM / HIGHER-RISK ITEMS

- **QUICK_WINS**: 
  - Execution Quality Scoring and spread depth vetoes (highly deterministic, easy to unit test).
  - Cost Model fee/spread estimation.
- **MEDIUM**:
  - Bounded Dynamic sizing.
  - RiskMode Hysteresis (requires careful state transitions in [gate.rs](file:///C:/Bot%20mk3/crates/bot-server/src/services/orchestrator/gate.rs)).
- **HIGHER_RISK**:
  - Net Edge Calibration: Mapping the ML model output [value](file:///C:/Bot%20mk3/crates/bot-server/src/services/orchestrator/leverage.rs#655-674) or `logit` predictably to roughly-calibrated `expected_move_bps`. This requires tuning the threshold scaling.

---

## P. EXPLICIT ASSUMPTIONS

1. **ASSUMPTION:** The standard ML policy outputs a [value](file:///C:/Bot%20mk3/crates/bot-server/src/services/orchestrator/leverage.rs#655-674) metric or logit that can be linearly mapped to `expected_move_bps` using a configurable calibration scalar.
2. **ASSUMPTION:** Execution Interface allows asynchronous sizing/limit price generation without introducing intolerable intra-tick latency over websocket.
3. **ASSUMPTION:** Existing Backtester framework can intercept new `EntryMode::Maker` limits directly through the existing [CommissionPolicy](file:///C:/Bot%20mk3/proto/bot.proto#789-806) bridging logic without needing a rewrite of the simulator's fill rules.
